The paper presents a novel machine learning classifier for multivariate time series classification. The approach involves feature extraction, feature selection, and machine learning classification. The paper is likely to be classified under cs.LG (Machine Learning), as it involves the development of a new classifier. It could also be classified under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves the use of machine learning techniques. Additionally, it could be classified under cs.DM (Data Mining) as it involves the extraction of features from data. The paper also mentions the use of computer vision techniques for motion gesture recognition, which could lead to a classification under cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks for classification, which could lead to a classification under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
